        "timestamp": "2019-09-24 13:25:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> The problem is not solved here I think.\n> \n> Let say, the default value is not \"\" or Null but some type value.\n> \n> The default value will directly override input and the resolution will not go through.\n\nDefault value can be anything, I didn't touch the processing logic.\n\nRather, added an explicit condition to check resolved value not to be Empty or Null so that it won't set it same.",
